Symbols
Symbols (c), (tm), and (r)  
HTML symbols can come in handy: &sect; &yen; &cent; &pound; &euro; &curren;  
Some (like the Dutch Florin symbol: &fnof;) may work in older browsers.  
Unicode symbols work too.
¥,£,€,¤,ƒ  
HTML white space: non-breaking_space:(&nbsp;) tab:(&Tab;)  
newline(&NewLine;) does not redder a newline. 
Many more HTML symbols referenced at:
More referenced at [Symbol Codes | Entity Codes for HTML](http://sites.psu.edu/symbolcodes/codehtml/)  
I'm not sure if all are supported by hugo's non-mmark markdown.  
Many of these are not supported by hugo. Maybe they can be enabled but I dont know.

